lexa.core.data

Class BaseDataSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • lexa.core.data.BaseDataSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<DataSet>, java.lang.Iterable<DataItem>, DataFactoryItem, DataSet
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArrayDataSet, HashDataSet

    public abstract class BaseDataSet
extends java.lang.Object
implements DataSet
    Provide the base methods for a data set.

    This provides the getters for the specific types supported. It does not implement the basic get method

    Author:
    william

      • item

        public DataValue item(java.lang.String key)
        Description copied from interface: DataSet
        Get a DataValue from anywhere in the hierarchical list.
        This allows safe access to a child item without checking that the parent DataSet exists. The syntax ds.item("parent.child") will check for the dataset parent and if it exists return the item child. If a parent does not exist it returns a null value. To access an item in an array use :n on the fields name to retrieve the nth item in the array.
        Specified by:
        item in interface DataSet
        Parameters:
        key - The dot separated hierarchical key for the DataItem.
        Returns:
        The DataValue if it exists, otherwise null.
